channel.description:
RuneScape-Radio has been sponsored by: [URL=http://google.com/refer/Manzarth][IMG]http://prodegebanners.sitegrip.com/images/google-468x60Alt1.jpg[/img][/URL]
Today on RuneScape-Radio we will be going online on RuneScape! Please feel free to join the whole RuneScape Radio team including myself! We decided that today the prize would be your own AMAX- Server tower! No more need for a VPS!
[b]Details on how to win the prize[/b]: Come into world 7 and find me in Varrock! I will be giving hints throughout the show! Show starts at 10am pacific time.
[IMG]http://i344.photobucket.com/albums/p348/tekidder_2008/00-Xn-0303.jpg[/img]
Features:
Supports one high performance Intel® Xeon® processor 3400 series, based on Intel® Core™ microarchitecture Also supports one cost effective 32nm Intel® Core™ i3, Intel® Pentium®, and Intel® Celeron® processor series, based on the new Intel® Core™ Microarchitecture Integrated PCI Express 2.0 I/O Integrated Memory Controller (IMC) Supports Intel® Turbo Boost & Intel® Hyper-Threading technologies Supports IPMI 2.0 with remote management capabilities, helping to lower IT operating costs while increasing system uptime Provides excellent internal storage and I/O flexibility Ideal to be used as an affordable platform for departmental, workgroups server, and business-critical database applications
call in number: 1(347) 994-3646 Direct station link: http://www.blogtalkradio.com/pavalyon/2010/05/12/runescape-radio-gossip main site link: http://www.runescapefans.tk
How the prizes work: Go to blogtalkradio.com and makean account as a radio hoster. They give you the option to give out prizes or not. If you say this then you need to pay $40.00 a month. All the prizes are provided by Blog Talk Radio
